rfly abundance to farms with smaller areas of these schemes (3926).\n\nOne UK study reported that providing advice to landowners about applying for an agri-environment scheme resulted in 82% of them submitting applications, with over 3,000 ha of farmland consequently being managed for the marsh fritillary butterfly (3846).",
